Thursday nights are popping! Get crunk or drunk and be amazed by the exhibits, sounds like a great idea to me. I really enjoy the thursday night events because it is really hard to go to museums during the day if you are working. Also instead of having kids run around screaming and yelling it is more of a socialable event with 21 and up people. Plus the mesuem area is always fun to be around!

LGs was the best place to have my birthday party. They were so accommodating and on top of things. Everyone was so impressed with the service and hospitality. There were at least 30 of us and our server was so on top of everyone’s orders and no one had to wait long for a drink or food. They also moved tables in the room as needed and rearranged the seating to accommodate the crowd. I was so happy and impressed with the night!
Staff is great
Had an amazing time at this spot ❤️

I ordered the caesar salad with steak. They cooked the steak to order and it was perfect! I especially liked that the lettuce was chopped small enough to avoid being clumsy as some salads can be. My friend had the blackened chicken sandwich and side salad. The chicken was spicy as expected and the salad was generously sized and served with balsamic vinaigrette.
Love the cozy tables by the fireplaces! Good happy hour menu. Cheese curds were especially good. The chicken pot pie is very large and delicious!

I was told to leave by the security because I was too drunk, bearing in mind that I had one drink at the bar. Security told me that a bar tender had told them I was too drunk and needed to leave, at which point I realised that I was being kicked out because I didn’t tip the bar tender. The drinks were really expensive, but I’m British and just moved to the U.S. and we don’t really tip bar tenders there because they get paid well and it’s just not our culture. Anyway I couldn’t believe how horrible I was treated and I will not be going back again.
A good bar with great cheap drinks on tap.
Good vibes. Good drinks. Good people
Didn't eat but the ccx service was great

A tale of two sandwiches. It’s a nice atmosphere. Prices are reasonable on drinks. It took about 40 minutes to get our pretzel appetizer.  We didn’t complain about the hour wait for food because it pushed us into happy hour. Both of us ordered chicken sandwiches. One was a big chicken breast. Mine was a thin small piece. The “guacamole spread” smelled like peas, not guacamole. Server was good. Very nice. Overall we enjoyed it.

The Lady Gregory’s in Andersonville is a million times better in every way (food, staff, and the vibe of the restaurant in general). I was excited when I learned they had an old town location but was extremely disappointed.  Food was subpar, staff was not attentive or very polite, and the place seemed to not know what theme they were going with or what they were trying to do. Giving an extra star just because the bouncer was very friendly.
Very rude staff
Good vibes, great customer service, and amazing food.
Awesome alfresco dining, dog friendly 🐕

The male bouncer is an absolute lunatic. I genuinely am scared to even say a single word in line in fear he will freak out at me and kick me out. Avoid this bar if you don't want to be verbally assaulted. This was not a one time instance i witness it happening every weekend to numerous groups in line. Disgusting
The service and all the employ

Sat at a table on a Monday night around 8pm. Was never served for 20 minutes, until we went to the bar to get menus. My food came out wrong. My burger was cooked well-done when I ordered t medium. Everyone else’s food seemed to be subpar for the prices. The fries were burnt/over-cooked, the fish and chips only came with 2 fish pieces, the fried pickles didn’t really have a fried coating and the pretzel app was small and not very good. Our server never came back to the table after dropping off the food. So no one could ask for condiments or another drink. We had to go get him to get our check after waiting awhile. And did want even want to ask him for separate checks because we did not feel like he could handle it. Also, we were not informed of the specials when we sat down so we all ordered overpriced food compared to what was available.
This place was delicious. The service was great. I had the ultimate grilled cheese, Brussels and cheese curds.

Always a great place to come in for a quiet beer. A rotating draft list makes frequent visits fun. The atmosphere is one of the best in old town and the food compliments it well. Also a great place for some whiskey.
Our server was very nice and our drinks were really good!! I love the feel of this place. The decor was great.
Bruching heaven.

My girlfriend and I were looking for a place where the sun would be in our face at the end of the day. This is the location that has it. We had a great meal with wonderful ambience. The drink menu was very nice. I only review The Best of the Best. Don't think about it, just go enjoy this place. Share and like.

I wouldn't call it a gastro pub but the food here is a cut above bar food.  Good potpie and club sandwich in our group as well as tasty crispy brussel sprouts.  Comfy atmosphere and plenty of TVs for the big game.

I was skeptical at first. We we're seated in a side booth for several minutes before a server welcomed us. But boy o boy, when that service hit, it was a thing of beauty. We had multiple employees check in on our experience and it was quite pleasant. The waitress was filled with humor as she greeted us with an upside down frown. The pretzels, soft and succulent. The nachos, ample. Would easily recommend.

I tried to get in with my military ID and was turned away....I was told they do not accept.  I had a group of 5 and we went elsewhere. Disappointed to find the first bar I’ve been to since being stationed here that does not accept our military.
They were the best when they first opened

Beautiful space with a really nice living room. Feel. In the back with a fireplace. It was kind of slow the evening we stopped in and service was acceptable. I'm sure if it was a more. Busy night the place would have a great vibe about it.
Food, service and vibe were great! We had the back room to ourselves and it was wonderful. The kalbi wings were delicious
Lived here al long time and just discovered.   Great place
Always a decent time. Some of the bartenders have attitudes but over all a good time.
I love that this place is an adult haven in the middle of bars that turn into clubs. The food is good and it's a larger than usual place for the area.
Great local joint. Recommend if you're trying to find somewhere new.
Service could definitely be improved but food was good

Worst experience at a bar, almost ruined our night. Two friends and I arrived early to get a big table against the wall to accommodate our large group.We informed our server as well as the hostess we were expecting more people. It got pretty busy after about an hour and our group arrived and was waiting outside in the line. My friend called me and said the door woman doesn't believe they had a table waiting for them - which is fine, doing your job I get it. BUT I went to get our server and we went to inform the door woman that she was serving us at a large table and we have been expecting those people. The door lady persited to just argue with the server and said since no one told her there were any available tables, they can't come in. ARE YOU ABSOLUTELY DUMB?!?! YOUR co-worker is telling you she has been expecting these people and you're going to stand there and take your job WAY to seriously?! We left immediately so we can join our party and ended up spending over $600 across the street. Way to drive out more revenue. Disorganized, rude, and plain ignorant.
Food so good and service nice  Kind of loud environment but good for GNO
Had small plates for an event I was attending. It was okay. Very quiet for a Monday.

Lunch menu is well done😁 However, the music is incredibly loud - could barely have a conversation with my friends. Hope the next time I stop by the sound is toned down a bit for daytime hours. Felt like I was at a club 😬
Great food, drinks, music, service and good ambience
Great service, the wings were awesome.
Rachel just gets it. 10/10 highly recommend Lady G’s

Really good music, lots of very young people but We liked the music so we stayed. Had couple of drinks and watched people having fun. One song I really liked and danced on one of those “couch top” made out of cement/tile. Bouncer approached me very aggressively and yelled I had to leave. Usually at any place they will give you a warning or tell you in a nice way. But he was rude, I apologize I didn’t know and even asked him if it was for real or if there was a chance to just get a warning, he said “no, leave now!!”. I asked if I could finish my drink, then my boyfriend and I left quíetly. We aren’t trouble people. Earlier, I saw another bouncer giving another client a warning for smoking inside the place and it was all good. I’ve never been kicked out of place and bc of dancing, ridiculous... now we now those tile/cement couch top are meant for who knows what. We’re not coming back or recommending this place to anyone. We’re from the neighborhood, this place is a no no for customer service. This place really needs to train their bouncers. There’s actually something called having the right approach.
Really loud

Service, drinks, and food top notch! Especially a fan of their cheddar artichoke dip. Yum! I don't understand all the negative reviews about food and service. I live around corner and always a positive experience, especially with our girl, Kelsey. I'll be back next Bingo Wednesday for sure!
Under new management, this place has gone downhill for me. Now it's just another loud, mediocre bar with subpar food choices.

The atmosphere of LG’s is outstanding. They have a very intimate and modern feel for an Irish pub. Great fit for old town / Wells St. interesting decor all around, with one room themed like a wine cellar and another lined with bookshelves.  The menu has some good options and interesting takes on what you might consider traditional bar food. I went with the short rib cheese burger and it was excellent. The presentation was decent and the quality of meet was very good. We did nachos and Brussels sprouts as an app and both were very good.  The service was decent. The server disappeared for periods of time and did not have any knowledge on the wines or whiskeys offered, but she was very friendly. For have a wine cellar themed room, I would expect a more extensive wine list. They only have about 6 different wines. Also, they have an expansive whiskey menu, but then were out of the first selection we ordered.  Overall, our experience was great. The atmosphere is impressive and the food was very good. I recommend getting some good wines on your menu and take Bogle off the list. You have the clientele that will buy it in old town.
Prime rib sandwich was delicious and fries were amazing. Decor and ambiance perfect for a nice Sunday lunch.  Thank you!

Terrible terrible terrible bar!!! This is worst bar in Old Town. Was dead at 10pm and the Staff was extremely rude - especially the dorman. There are so many great bars in the area- do NOT waste ur time here!!!

Out of all the bars in Old Town- this is by far the worst! The service is terrible starting from the completely unprofessional and rude dorman. If you are looking for a fun night out with friends- avoid this place at all costs!

Went here around 10pm on a Friday, inside was dark & had bad service. Security was incredibly rude upon entry, especially for how lame this place was. Bar next door the Vig was so much better, recommend that place over this hands down.

Terrible service-extremely rude staff. Bar has a weird vibe and set up.  Def not some place I would recommend. I’ve lived in the area for over 10 years and  there are so many other great bars in the area- don’t waste ur time here!!

Excellent all around!  Great service, great food and great atmosphere! After having traveled the country for years, this is hands down in my top 3 places. Will be definitely coming back.

For a city that has a lot of great burger options, I went into my burger order with pretty moderate expectations. However, I was very impressed with what I got. I don't normally get bacon and a ton of toppings on mine, but the cheese worked so well with the meats that I ended up loving it. Don't miss out on the burger.

Excellent food, friendly staff, good beer and wine selection, and especially an awesome aesthetic. The only thing I hate is the music selection. Doesn't fit the vibe at all...too clubby. But if you can ignore that (or I guess if you like that music), it's great there.

Great place and food and the bar is gorgeous. The entrance was a bit tough to find.  Both my friend and I both accidentally went to the restaurant next door. Love the name but adding the word Irish in the signage might help people know that it's an Irish pub. Hope they do well in this location.

Lady Gregory's is a fun surprise Irish pub. The food menu is larger and better than a typical Irish Pub. We had a variety of food and they were all wonderful! We even tried a sampling of desserts and they were awesome!  My only personal complaint: How do you have an Irish pub that doesn't serve Harp Beer from Guiness???  Our evening was wonderful and we plan to head back!

Good service and really nice decore. For the holidays they decorate very nicely. It has a few spaces with fireplaces for the cozy or romantic feel. The drinks, appetizers and desserts are good.
The food wad delicious. Friendly service. I recommend the beer flight and the Portobello reuben.

The food was excellent and came out fast. The drinks were good too. I went here for my birthday dinner and even made a reservation ahead of time at the right location so that I could get a spot near a fireplace and when we got there they told me they didnt have my reservation. I dont believe that but I didnt let it sour my dinner. The ambience was great and so was the music. They spent a lot of money renovating the space and its beauty shows. The server was a little weird however and he spent most of night gliding in and sliding away from our table. My friend said he was creepy. I told her he probably either had worked all day or had a couple cocktails because he was happy. Overall I give Lady Gregorys a 4 because  have been here before and it was really wonderful and the staff were really great. The food is excellent for irish pub food and well worth the price. Its a great date night spot and girls night out dinner. I would not bring large groups here 5+ unless i called several days in advance.

Always great food and a really great Irish Pub decor.   I heard part of the woodwork was sent here from Ireland.  Big bar and two nice sitting areas in the back where groups can hang out- drink, talk w/o feeling like you're in the middle of a huge bar

Dined as part of a group in the smaller back room. Our server Amy was excellent. The few apps I tried, flat bread and curried fries, were tasty. My entree was the Scottish salmon and my dates was the Rosemary chicken. Both were excellent and done properly. But really the best part of the meal was the great selection of whiskeys of which our group had some many. The cocktails were also very good and the folks that had wine did enjoy.
Very friendly and knowledgeable bar staff. Great beer selection. The Brussels sprouts and pot pie are fantastic. Nicely decorated for the holidays.

Lovely atmosphere with a warm buzz of conversation, unlike loud sports bars nearby. We were also in a time crunch, and our waitress did well to keep things moving for us.

LOVE this place!!!!! The atmosphere is so nice and cozy, and makes you forget you're in the middle of the city. The service was great, and so was the food. Love that they have fun ciders on tap as well. My new go to place!

Food is overpriced for what it is. And I'm the type of person who doesn't mind paying up for good food. So many better restaurant options are in the area just a few steps away. Doesn't live up to my expectations for a restaurant in the Old Town/Wells Street area. The good thing is it's one of the few places in the area that doesn't blast music at such a loud volume you can't have a conversation. Lots of beers on draft and a lengthy spirits book. Okay spot for a drink but skip the food. Deviled eggs were meh, cheese curds were good but could do without the cinnamon on top, chopped salad was meh and fish & chips were meh. Cocktails were just okay and should probably be a buck or two cheaper. After $86 I felt like I was overpaying for typical bar food.
Typical American style bar/restaurant... Food ok.

Fantastic food and an impressive spirits list. We ducked in right before seeing a play at A Red Orchid Theater and the staff had us in and out in under 45 min. Will definitely be going back to try their whiskey selection.

Nice atmosphere and polite waitress. The menu offers a large selection between brunch, eggs or burger. The burrito is a good price-value !  Wouldn't recommend the Irish hash however that felt like a really small dish for the same price.

A spacious, well appointed place in the center of everything in Old Town, a rotating roster of beers, a well-stocked bar, and a few good menu options.
Bad quality meat quality in burger. Not true at Wilde and LG in Andersonville.

Fun place and great service.  Food is excellent.

A lot of places come and go in this location and I don't see Lady Gregory's to be any different. Given all the great food options in the area, this just seemed to be overpriced bar food. I was a little surprised when my friend and I both left paying over $50 for sandwiches that were just ok and couple glasses of mediocre wine. For the kind of food and drinks they are serving, save your money or get a more satisfying meal by going to any of the restaurants just steps away.
Cool place.

Great esthetic, well decorated and cool vibe, good drink selection. Went on a Saturday night and the music was way too loud and the AC was too cranked up, but would definitely go back for a dinner or date night. Lot of potential with this bar. My recommendation: turn down the music and cater to a different audience. With douchey bars like Benchmark and the Vig all up and down Wells St, there's really no middle-ground bars in Old Town (aka between a post-college frat party and being an alcoholic in your 60s.) You guys could reach a very real audience of young people looking for a fun time in a cool part of Chicago but are a little disenfranchised by the current choices.
They know how to keep time
